cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the application of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for saliency prediction, which is a common task in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a modular system for the CNNs, which involves training the encoder and decoder separately, and using multiple CNN models with different architectures or pre-trained on different datasets. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which deal with the development and application of machine learning algorithms. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on three public saliency benchmarks, which suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
